page.title: 09Transport Train and Coach
page.content:
{The Railway Station {Twenty}trains per day stop at Tisbury station and on average{sixty {five}tickets per day are sold. The earliest train is the 05.58 and the latest is the 22.55. The trains run to {London}in one direction and the{West {Country}in the other. A new loop line is hoped to be built soon. The station has been in service since 1859.
{Nadder Valley Coaches The coaches take children to school and on request will take people on outings all over the country. The earliest coach leaves at 08.15 and goes to{Shaftesbury.}The latest leaves at 19.45 and goes to{Gillingham. There are 14 coaches altogether, including their parent company Levers. The coach station was built in 1945.
